<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-22T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-22T14:00:00-05:00" n="881" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d881">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/12963.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Brazilian Minister</gloss> to Mexico.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-22T14:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 22, 1914, 2 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Please call upon Carranza personally if possible, otherwise on Foreign
                            Office, and urge the avoidance of anything which could be construed as a
                            lack of courtesy to the diplomatic representatives. It is very important
                            that whatever he finds it necessary to do should be done with due regard
                            to diplomatic usage and respect to the diplomatic character of foreign
                            representatives. Airy other course of action might involve him in
                            serious foreign complications.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>